This is a good collection of classic comedies from Universal. Animal House and Blues Brothers are true classics and are hilarious (everyone miss John Belushi?). The Jerk is an interesting movie with Steve Martin playing the gullible, village idiot so well (his fake drunk voice is horrible and quite annoying). Car Wash was definitely my least favorite of the four. I think it's interesting that Richard Pryor is listed as essentially the main character (the way it's promoted), yet he has what a 5 minute cameo part in the entire movie that comes with no lead-up and leaves with no follow-up. Overall really good collection of classic comedies with legendary comedians.

My Father was wanting "The Jerk" it for a while now, and my Mother and i were looking it up and came across this 4 pack but she said that all 4 of them are awesome movies, I must say that I would have to agree!
These movies are must haves if you love comedy. It will make you cry laughing at the best actors in comedy.

I saw this at a B & N store for about $20 when I was looking for Animal House. Three of my favorite comedies and one I never really watched before. I couldn't afford to buy them right there, so I looked for a used copy online and found a copy here for less than $10--and that's including the shipping & handling! The only disappointment is the edition of The Blues Brothers is the expanded version and not anniversary edition that has both the original theatrical version and the longer cut. Other than that, a fine package and more affordable than getting them separately.
